      <p>这是一个生命的保护，这是一种解脱，我没得做个手术。</p>
      <p align="center">* * * * * * * * </p>
      <h3><strong><img src="<%= asset_path('darrelllee.jpg') %>" width="400" height="533"><br>
          Darrell Lee </strong></h3>
      <p><em>Hapeville, GA<br>
          July, 2010
      </em></p>
      <p>I was employed at a job where we made heavy-duty engine parts, requiring me to do heavy lifting. I had been lifting these parts for years until one time I felt a severe pain in my back. </p>
      <p>It happened on a Friday. When I got up Saturday morning, the pain went from my waist all the way down to my ankle. The pain was a tingling and sharp pain. I just could not do anything--couldn't walk, bend, pick up anything--and I could obviously not work. </p>
      <p>I was diagnosed with herniated discs, sciatica, and a spondylolisthesis with severe disc degeneration. A chiropractor adjusted me and put E-Stim pads on my back every day for two weeks, but the pain did not get better. It did not work. </p>
      <p>After seventeen treatments with IDD Therapy &reg; , my pain has gone from 10 out of 10 to about 3 out of 10. I can shop for food and I can walk, whereas before I could not go due to extreme pain. I can clean my house without pain and do most housework. </p>            <h3 align="center">* * * * * * * * </h3>
      <h3>Ned Hardin </h3>
      <p><em>Riverdale, GA<br>
          June, 2010 </em></p>
      <p><img src="<%= asset_path('nedhardin.jpg') %>" width="194" height="204" hspace="4" align="left">My pain came on gradually over the years. &nbsp; I had spent time in the military and played football in high school and was accustomed to being pretty active. &nbsp; I tried physical therapy. Spinal injections only helped for a month, and the pain came right back. </p>
      <p>None of the treatments I tried helped me. I eventually got to the point where I just wanted to stay in due to the extreme pain. My social life was crushed, I could not sit or stand, I couldn't lie down, work out or even go for a walk. &nbsp; Everything was painful. I began to gain weight, which didn't help. &nbsp;&nbsp; My pain level was a 9 out of 10! &nbsp; I had pain shooting down both legs and sharp pain in my knee. &nbsp; I was in agony whenever I tried to drive; it felt like a stake was being driven through my back. After treatment ... the numbness, tingling and pain is gone! &nbsp; I am walking up to 3 miles at a time now! &nbsp; Before treatment I could not even walk 20 feet without severe pain! &nbsp; I have lost 30 pounds now that I can exercise and my overall health has improved. My blood pressure dropped from 160/100 to 120/70! &nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
      <p>It has dramatically changed my life for the better. </p>
      <p align="center">* * * * * * * * </p>
      <h3>Manish Aggarwal </h3>
      <p><em>Atlanta, GA<br>
          June, 2010 </em></p>
      <p>I played a bit of tennis, basketball and volleyball. My pain came on gradually and appeared to be a wearing down of my back. It started in my lower back first, then pain began to go down my left leg. It got to a point where I could barely walk. I experienced incredible pain whenever I tried to lift something. I was diagnosed with a herniated disc and started physical therapy and medications. The physical therapy helped improve my core strength, but it did not get to my pain. Since starting treatment...I am off medications. I am able to lift more weight, walk, sit and even run with minimal pain. This treatment has improved my willingness to leave the house and go out more. My quality of life has greatly improved. </p>
      <p align="center">* * * * * * * * </p>
      <h3>Todd Grubb </h3>
      <p><em>Waleska, GA<br>
          June, 2010 </em></p>
      <p>I was on my motorcycle and got rear-ended by a Lexus while waiting for the light to turn green. I was in constant pain, with a level between 8 and 9 out of 10. I was unable to work proficiently. I am a mechanic, and I was unable to do the simple things such as lift wheels to rotate tires or even pick up a car battery. My pain was constant. I was unable to sleep. I couldn't get the pain to stop. I could not do water sports or any other activity. &nbsp; After being diagnosed with three herniated discs, I tried aquatic therapy, physical therapy, electrical stimulation, flexeril (3-4 per day), and hydrocodone (3-4 per day). Nothing seemed to work. &nbsp; Epidural Injections were the next treatment recommended before I saw a cable infomercial about DiscForce(TM) with IDD Therapy&reg;. </p>
      <p>I came into the doctor's office with excruciating pain between 8-9, and now my pain level is between 0-1. I am no longer dependent on any type of pain medication or muscle relaxer. I am able to return to work and actively do the same type of work I did prior to my disc injuries. &nbsp; I am excited to have my life back! I would highly recommend DiscForce with IDD Therapy as an alternative to surgery. &nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
      <p align="center">* * * * * * * * </p>
      <h3>Sandra Hogan </h3>
      <p><em>Hampton, GA<br>
          March, 2010 </em></p>
      <p>My back pain started when I was working at the Holiday Inn back in 1983. I was lifting heavy furniture and other things when I injured my back, and I've had pain ever since. </p>
      <p>The pain was bad enough that I wasn't able to do housework or the arts and crafts I love to do, and I could not sketch or paint. </p>
      <p>I was diagnosed with a herniated disc and had to have a hip replacement in my right hip. </p>
      <p>I tried injections, pain pills, and electrical stimulation, but the pain would always come back. </p>
      <p>But after 20 treatments with IDD Therapy, I am now pain-free! I'm able to do artwork and crafts. I'm having more fun--dancing, traveling, etc. I am happier without pain. I wish I could have had this therapy a long time ago. </p>
      <p>I'd recommend IDD highly--to ANYONE that has back pain. It WORKS! </p>
      <p align="center">* * * * * * * * </p>
      <h3><img src="<%= asset_path('spicer.jpg') %>" width="400" height="370">James Spicer </h3>
      <p><em>Eatonton, GA<br>
          March, 2010 </em></p>
      <p>I've had back pain since 1980, when I ruptured three discs while demonstrating a boom lift. I experienced excruciating pain for decades. There were periods of several months where I couldn't walk. On two separate occasions, I was confined to a bed for six months, taking muscle relaxers and pain killers just so I could sleep. </p>
      <p>The pain was so intense that I was unable to stand up for more than two minutes. I couldn't walk to the mailbox; in fact, I had to use the lawn tractor to go to the mailbox and to walk my dog. The pain would be so excruciating sometimes that I had to crawl to the bathroom; three times the pain was so severe that I was taken to the hospital in an ambulance to get a shot of Darvon. </p>
      <p>My pain was so bad that just getting into my truck was work. I would grip the steering wheel so tight because the pain was so severe. I had to get into a motorized wheelchair just to shop at Wal-Mart. </p>
      <p>In 1994 I took pain medication and anti-inflammatories. I also received nerve blocks for a few months, but they were only a temporary relief, just a Band-Aid. </p>
      <p>My wife read about IDD Therapy &reg; treatment in a local newspaper. Since it is non-invasive and involves no medication, my wife got on the Internet to learn more, and five days later I was on the table receiving IDD Therapy &reg; treatments. After three treatments, I was down from 12 hydrocodone pills per day to zero, and I haven't had any since the third treatment. </p>
      <p>I came into treatment with a pain level of 10 and now, after 25 treatments, I am down to a 1. </p>
      <p>I'm now able to walk my dog, do yard work, and wash dishes. &nbsp; I am back in the church choir. &nbsp; IDD Therapy &reg; treatment allows me to live a more fruitful life; when you are productive, your self-worth and self-esteem are higher. My wife is happier, too. </p>
      <p>You'd better try IDD Therapy &reg; treatment, because it will be one of the best decisions of your life. The very first treatment made a believer out of me. I was blessed by reading about IDD Therapy &reg; in the newspaper, and maybe I can help someone. Maybe someone will be blessed by my success. My entire family is excited that I have gotten my life back. If I could take the machine home, I would find room for it. </p>
      <p align="center">* * * * * * * * </p>
      <h3>Julie Bruce </h3>
      <p><em>Jackson, GA<br>
          March, 2010 </em></p>
      <p>I had long-term severe back pain for years, even after spinal-fusion surgery in March of 2000. My pain was so severe as to cause me to become disabled. I was diagnosed with a herniated disc, bulging discs, and sciatica, as well as tingling and numbness in my hands. I tried all types of back-pain treatments, including the DRS, which only continued the cycle of pain and a debilitating lifestyle. </p>
      <p>But after 20 treatments of IDD Therapy, there is dramatically less pain and much more mobility. I may even be able to teach again as a computer-networking engineer after seven years of being unable to do so because of my back pain. </p>
      <p>I am finally happy again--"It brought the music and hope back to me." Everybody can see the "glow" on my face. </p>
      <p>IDD is a miracle treatment and will give you your life back. </p>
      <p>My mind is clearer and my short-term memory is much, much better. Everything about my life is MUCH better. I have hope again!! Now I will finally be able to play with my six-year-old granddaughter. I missed most of the early years, but now is a new beginning. I also will be able to pick up my one-month-old grandson and be able to see all of the "firsts" that I missed with my granddaughter. I got my FAMILY back, too! </p>
      <p>Now with IDD--the answer is YES!! </p>
