      <h3><img src="<%= asset_path('ammiehampton.jpg') %>" width="200" height="199" hspace="4" align="left">Ammie Hampton </h3>
      <p><em>Greensboro, GA<br>
          October, 2009 </em></p>
      <p>I had been going to the chiropractor for ten years as a result of a ruptured disc. The pain was so constant, I was unable to sleep in the bed. I tried to sleep on my right side with pain medication, but still I had no relief. I was unable to dishwashing or laundry and couldn't walk 20 feet without my back burning. I'd been working full-time, but because of the pain, I was relegated to part-time work. </p>
      <p>I saw a chiropractor and received medication, but the treatment gave me no relief. The situation was so bad, my mother-in-law suggested that I use a cane. My husband wanted me to use a wheelchair. My six and ten-year-old boys wanted to know when their mom's back was going to get better because they could see her in pain and they could not play football, tennis, or run with me. </p>
      <p>On a scale of one to ten, my pain level was a ten. But after 22 treatments of IDD Therapy, I can sleep on my back and sides now. I'm able to clean up the house. I feel as if I'm on the path to getting my life back. And, of course, my husband is glad I'm able to sleep in the bed with him now! </p>
      <p>I would highly recommend that anyone who's seeking treatment for back pain should try IDD Therapy. </p>
