      <h3>Frederick H. Spoehrer </h3>
      <p><em>Greensboro, GA<br>
          September, 2009 </em></p>
      <p>I experienced intense back pain after I slipped in the shower 18 months ago and fractured several of my ribs. I was confined to a wheelchair for six months, and my family had to come in from Detroit to help me get around. </p>
      <p>My back was so arched, it was painful for me to straighten up. When I would lay on my back, it would look like I was sitting up. I needed several pillows to prop up my back because I couldn't straighten it out. I was so hunched-over while walking, my head was down at knee level. I could not see where I was walking and could only shuffle my feet approximately four to six inches at a time. </p>
      <p>In addition to my fractured ribs, I was diagnosed with arthritis, osteoporosis, and muscle spasms. I went to a chiropractor for electrical stimulation and massage therapy, but the treatment didn't seem to do any good. There was no improvement in my pain. </p>
      <p>After seventeen treatments of IDD Therapy, I can walk straight up without a cane. I'm starting to get my normal stride back. I can get in and out of my car and drive it now. I can actually hold my head back now and see the sun. </p>
      <p>IDD Therapy is a wonderful treatment, and it has helped me tremendously. I have told a lot of people with back pain that I am convinced IDD Therapy can help them. I would recommend IDD Therapy to anyone with back pain. </p>
